    "explanation_english": "The Scheduled Castes and The Scheduled Tribes (Prevention of Atrocities) Act, 1989, commonly known as the PoA Act or SC/ST Act, is a special law enacted by the Parliament of India to prevent atrocities against Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes. It aims to deliver justice to these communities through proactive efforts to enable them to live with dignity and self-esteem and without fear, violence, or suppression. The Act is structured into 5 Chapters and comprises 23 Sections, detailing various offences, penalties, special courts, and other provisions for the protection of SC/ST rights.",
