    "explanation_english": "According to Section 144(4) of the Criminal Procedure Code, 1973, an order passed under Section 144 shall not remain in force for more than two months from the date it is made. However, the State Government, if it deems necessary for public safety or to prevent disturbances, can extend this period by notification in the Official Gazette for a further period not exceeding six months from the date on which the Magistrate's order would have otherwise expired. Therefore, the initial period is 2 months, and the State Government can extend it up to a maximum of 6 months.",
